Missy (Also known as Missy Quest in Japan) was an arcade game designed by a Venezuelan development team under a cheap contract to capitalize on the popularity of the character of "Missy". The game was rushed, releasing with a bug that caused the titular character to not spawn during gameplay. This resulted in outcry from the public, who vandalized most machines. Now the few remaining serve as decorations in various retro hangout spots and skate parks. A relic of olden days.
